external_knowledge:
- "shining stars in their category" refers to products with high efficiency within their category;
- "ability to adapt to price changes" refers to price elasticity of demand;
- "top two in each category" refers to the products with the highest efficiency ranks within their respective categories;
- "efficiency surpasses the average price elasticity" means the current efficiency of the product is greater than the average price elasticity of demand across all products.

- 'blossoms' refers to products in the database;
- 'grown stronger' refers to products whose current efficiency is greater than their baseline efficiency;
- 'high responsiveness to market changes' refers to products with a price elasticity greater than 0.5.

sql:
SELECT AVG(em.price_elasticity) AS average_price_elasticity
FROM elasticity_metrics em
WHERE em.product_id = (
    SELECT MAX(product_id) 
    FROM products
);

